The paper deals with mutual exclusion algorithms for shared-memory systems, which is a topic in distributed computing (cs.DC) and data structures (cs.DS). The focus on performance metrics and algorithm design also suggests categories such as operating systems (cs.OS) and programming languages (cs.PL). The mention of a weak adversary and abort signals suggests a focus on fault tolerance and system resilience, which could fall under the category of systems and control (cs.SY).
